```xml
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.facebookpostingbot">

    <!-- 
        This manifest file is designed for the Facebook Posting Management Automation Tool.
        The application automates content scheduling and management on social media platforms, ensuring 24/7 operations.
        The following permissions and components are registered to enable seamless automation features.
    -->

    <!-- 
        This powerful permission enables the application to access the internet, 
        essential for interacting with Facebook's services for content management and scheduling.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    
    <!-- 
        Comprehensive capability for reading device storage, 
        which allows the application to manage media files for scheduling and posting.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    
    <!-- 
        This permission is crucial for writing to device storage, 
        enabling the application to save logs or media files generated during the automation processes.
    -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="Facebook posting bot - Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/AppTheme">

        <!-- 
            The MainActivity serves as the entry point of the application, 
            providing a user-friendly interface for managing social media content and scheduling.
        -->
        <activity android:name=".MainActivity">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
            The AutomationService operates in the background, 
            enabling continuous 24/7 content scheduling and posting capabilities. 
            This service ensures that the automation tasks run reliably without user intervention.
        -->
        <service android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:enabled="true"
            android:exported="false" />

    </application>

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Features:
- **Permissions**: 
  - The manifest declares permissions necessary for network access and file management, which are vital for social media operations.
  
- **Component Registration**: 
  - **MainActivity** provides an interactive interface for users, while **AutomationService** continuously manages background tasks, ensuring a seamless experience with MadHubâ€™s powerful automation.

This configuration ensures compliance with Android standards while highlighting MadHub's capabilities for efficient social media management.
